div.p:
On July the 13th of that Year, was John Rouse brought to Tryal. Against him there was ample


Evidence given. First by Thomas Lea; 
                  That the said Rouse undertook to provide 100 Arms for the City-Divisions: That he said, Nothing could be done unless the King were seiz'd; adding, We remember Forty One, when the King went and set up his Standard; therefore we will seize them that they shall not set up their Standard.
